Mass went UP. The substitution adds an extra lambda. Let me reconsider.

Better alternative: rather than refactoring `quoteStep`, observe that `policyBase + surcharges = sumBy(billables, itemPremium)`. So:

```ts
const quoteStep = (customer, quoteIndex, items) => {
  const billables = billingItems(items);
  const policyBase = sumBy(billables, basePremiumForItem);
  const subtotal = sumBy(billables, itemPremium);
  const discount = policyBase * policyDiscountRate(customer, quoteIndex);
  return { premium: Math.ceil(subtotal - discount + PROCESSING_FEE) };
};
```

This is clearer: `subtotal` = sum of full per-item premiums, then subtract discount, add fee. No need for `surcharges` intermediate.

